======================
Selenium Client Driver
======================

Introduction
============

Python language bindings for Selenium WebDriver.

The `selenium` package is used automate web browser interaction from Python.

+-----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **Home**: | http://www.seleniumhq.org                                                         |
+-----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **Docs**: | `selenium package API <http://selenium.googlecode.com/git/docs/api/py/api.html>`_ |
+-----------+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

This is the backward "py" module for Python 2.4 (for example RHEL5 / Centos 5),  it supports WebDriver Remote protocol. Browsers/drivers are not yet supported.

Supported Python Versions
=========================

* Python 2.4

Installing
==========

If you have git on your system, you can simply clone only py module::

    git init selenium
    cd selenium
    git remote add -f origin https://github.com/BlackSmith/selenium.git
    git config core.sparsecheckout true
    echo py/ >> .git/info/sparse-checkout
    git pull origin master


Alternately, you can download whole the source distribution from `GitHub <https://github.com/BlackSmith/selenium/archive/master.zip>`.


Example 0:
==========

from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.common.desired_capabilities \
        import DesiredCapabilities

driver = webdriver.Remote(\
        command_executor='http://selenium-hub.example.com:4444/wd/hub',
        desired_capabilities=DesiredCapabilities.FIREFOX)

driver.get('http://www.google.com')
driver.save_screenshot('screenshot.png')
driver.quit()

